act.article:
 2 Definitions. 

1 In these regulations, unless the context otherwise requires: 

 a Act means the Insurance Act, 1938 (4 of 1938); 
 b Actuarial Society of India means Actuarial Society of India constituted under Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860); 
 c Actuary means an individual possessing such qualifications as specified in Regulation 3; 
 d Authority means Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority established under the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority Act, 1999 (41 of 1999). 


2 All words and expressions used and not defined herein shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in the Insurance Act, 1938 (4 of 1938) or in the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority Act, 1999 (41 of 1999), or in the Regulations made thereunder.
